    "client_msg_id": "61c13d1a-199d-48e9-815a-17715c13ed79",
    "text": "If you learn how to get abstraction-averse folks to address boundary objects as signified and not as signifier, let me know. I yearn for this technology too. But I agree that drawing pictures together is our best stop-gap in the meantime.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1726102208.402909",
