    "text": "<@UC2A2ARPT>: I'm converted. I just went through and switched the last year+ of posts on my site replacing bare URLs with some descriptive text.\n\n<@UJBAJNFLK>: I spent some time researching it yesterday, and it's definitely not nothing under Linux. There's OS integration built in for say the Orca screenreader, which the OS will use if you install it. You do still have to install it, though. Also I ran into an error, so there's that.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1726012140.489089",
    "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "ECeC4",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "user",
                "user_id": "UC2A2ARPT"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ": I'm converted. I just went through and switched the last year+ of posts on my site replacing bare URLs with some descriptive text.\n\n"
              },
              {
                "type": "user",
                "user_id": "UJBAJNFLK"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ": I spent some time researching it yesterday, and it's definitely not nothing under Linux. There's OS integration built in for say the Orca screenreader, which the OS will use if you install it. You do still have to install it, though. Also I ran into an error, so there's that."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
