  {
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1726214315.995389",
    "client_msg_id": "636f1161-23e2-4624-b801-d7e3b55a24cb",
    "text": "Thanks <@UCUSW7WVD> for investigating!\n\nI didn't mean to imply that there is nothing for Linux. One screen reader I have been aware of for years is <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emacspeak|EmacSpeak> (for Emacs). But there is nothing \"built in\", and thus no obvious default that people would turn to.\n\nOrca looks more mainstream than EmacSpeak, being part of the GNOME universe. I don't use GNOME, but I could easily set up a second account on my machine using GNOME and Orca, and use that for testing. So... you have answered my question!",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1726012140.489089",
    "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "gXKQS",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Thanks "
              },
              {
                "type": "user",
                "user_id": "UCUSW7WVD"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " for investigating!\n\nI didn't mean to imply that there is nothing for Linux. One screen reader I have been aware of for years is "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emacspeak",
                "text": "EmacSpeak"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " (for Emacs). But there is nothing \"built in\", and thus no obvious default that people would turn to.\n\nOrca looks more mainstream than EmacSpeak, being part of the GNOME universe. I don't use GNOME, but I could easily set up a second account on my machine using GNOME and Orca, and use that for testing. So... you have answered my question!"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "linking-together",
    "channel_id": "C5U3SEW6A"
  },
  {
